
Lab Inventory: Asset Management

- All devices are segregated in domains
- 2-ways to import devices
     1> Manually one-by-one
     2> Import CSV file
- Add devices to Envs

Add New Device (Manually):
   - Add-Device
   - Delete-Device
   - Export Devices to CSV
   - Import CSV devices
   - Add Devices To Env
   - Create/Remove Filters
        - Device-Types
        - Device-Locations
        - Device-Vendors
   - Add / Remove Custom Fields

Import CSV devices:
   - In Lab Inventory, click "Export Devices To CSV" to get all the default headers
   - If any value have spaces, must put words inside double-quotes  <-- IMPORTANT!

   Adding custom fields:
       - To add custom fields, create the addtional fields first
       - Then export the csv file

 
Lab Inventory (Asset Management):
   - Status 
       Red:   Unreachable
       Green: Reachable
   - Name
   - Device Type
   - Vendor
   - Model
   - Serial #
   - Location
   - IP Address
   - IP Port
   - Login name
   - Password
   - Connection Protocol (SSH | Telnet)
   - Ports
        - Add-Ports
        - Remove-Ports
        - Add-Ports-To-Port-Group (Create Port-Groups first)
        - Remove-Ports-From-Port-Group
        - Connect-Ports-To-Device
        - Disconect-Device
        - Add / Remove Fields

        Port-Mgmt
           - Src-Ports
           - Connected-To-Device
           - Connected-To-Port
           - Port-Type
           - VLAN
           - Port-Speed
           - Port-Groups
           - PG-Multi-Tenant
           - Additional-Custom-Fields

   - Notes
   - User defined addtional fields


Adding Additional Fields for all devices and port-mgmt:
    - In Inventory, on the top toolbar, click "Add / Remove Fields"
    - Add a new field name, select the type (boolean or options)
    
    Option: 
        - Create a list of options for users to select
        - Separate words with a comma
        - Define the default option. Defaults to the first item

    Boolean: True | Boolean: False


Add / Remove Field Options
   - Allows users to add or remove field options 

   